{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It first generates region proposals and then classifies these regions.",
    "Therefore, two-stage object detection has higher accuracy but slower detection speed.",
    "Examples of two-stage object detection frameworks include Region-based Convolutional Neural Network (RCNN) [15], Spatial Pyramid Pooling Network (SPPNet) [16], Fast Convolutional Neural Network (Fast-RCNN) [17], Faster Convolutional Neural Network (Faster RCNN) [17], Feature Pyramid Network (FPN) [18] and Mask Region-based Convolutional Neural Network (Mask RCNN) [19].The second type is single-phase object detection, which directly generates the category probabilities and position coordinates of an object in a single phase.",
    "Single-phase object detection is simpler than two-phase object detection because it does not require a region proposal process.",
    "This is the reason why single-stage object detection has higher detection speed but lower accuracy."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Examples of two-stage object detection frameworks include Region-based Convolutional Neural Network (RCNN) [15], Spatial Pyramid Pooling Network (SPPNet) [16], Fast Convolutional Neural Network (Fast-RCNN) [17], Faster Convolutional Neural Network (Faster RCNN) [17], Feature Pyramid Network (FPN) [18] and Mask Region-based Convolutional Neural Network (Mask RCNN) [19].The second type is single-phase object detection, which directly generates the category probabilities and position coordinates of an object in a single phase."
